reviews.text:
Delighted by the friendly service and homemade, tasty food at a relaxed restaurant in Kimberling City. I have yet to try the pizza, but based on how much I enjoyed the Parmesan's salad, I will be trying their pizza soon!
Ate here with two friends the first week of April and each of us were thrilled with our choices. The large, Parmesan's salad is so filling and packed with fresh, delicious ingredients! I even added a few shakes of red pepper flakes and sprinkled parmesan cheese over the second half of my salad which took it to another level. One friend enjoyed her buffalo wings commenting how nicely prepared they were for her. Our other friend was full after enjoying the hot Italian sub on freshly baked bread. All 3 of us really enjoyed our tasty meals. We came in for an early lunch and were thankful it wasn't too busy. They also have a nice patio / deck with an overview of beautiful Table Rock Lake in the distance. We're planning on a return trip soon to try some freshly made pizza at Parmesan's. Surely it'll be a treat.
Great pizza and service. We got the mushroom burger and sausage pizza, with dessert and sides to go. Beers were cold and served with frosty mugs.

Incredible place- incredible food. Had the Parmeseana Deluxe salad- huge & full of yummy ingredients....plenty for 2 or 3 people.  Paired it eith the Mediterranean thin crust- wow. This place is a hidden gem! Oh & the new patio has a beautiful Lakeview  & a good vibe!

Parmesan‚Äôs had great food and incredible service. Our server was kind, helpful, and attentive. I asked for something not on the menu and he promptly checked and found they were able to make it! Very good, great portions, and incredible view.

Waited 2 and 1/2 hours for a delivery. After the first hour and 1/2 we called just to be sure it was being delivered and they said that it was out for delivery. Called again at 8 when they closed and just offered a refund or a delivery essentially just admitting what we already knew. Wish they would have just told us the first hour that it wasn't ACTUALLY out for delivery. Usually love eating this place but man what a bad way for us to end the weekend. I feel the rating is a fair trade for making my family miss dinner in a timely manor this evening.

detailedReviews.author: Jason Caudillo
detailedReviews.text:
My family was looking for a nice evening meal and after some research, we decided to stop by Parmesans Pizzeria. The location and feel is nice, rural and authentic. We decided to order a Large Sicilian Pizza along with some cheesy breadsticks.

The cheesy breadsticks were amazing. They had ample amounts of cheese and were quite plentiful portion wise. I enjoyed the burnt cheese in the outside while the center was cheesy and soft.

The Sicilian Pizza was very delicious. The pizza was cooked to perfection with a toasted crust on the outside. I am told that the pizza dough is homemade and based on the first bite, it was quite apparent. You could most certainly taste the quality which is leaps and bounds above any chain pizza restaurant.

Lastly, the service was wonderful. Our waitress, who I am assuming was the owner was incredibly kind and was attentive to our needs. I highly recommend stopping by if you are in the area and want a wonderful Italian experience with an authentic, rural charm.
